                <head>No. 157.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 263.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 478, of October 10,
                    last, in regard to mob violence against missionaries at Kwai Ping, and desire to
                    approve your admirable, as well as judicially expressed views upon the subject.
                    I am, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
